    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Theory is that the increase in CPU usage seen when Altair activated on the first devnet was because of the significant increase in gossip traffic because of sync committees. Given a 10,000 validator network and running 1000 on each box, they would be subscribed to all attestation subnets all the time, but that would only give about 312 single attestations per slot.\n\nWith sync committees there are 512 validators in the committee each producing a signature every slot which are spread over 4 subnets. If you wind up on all 4 subnets which is definitely possible you wind up more than doubling the amount of gossip traffic to verify (and have to generate and sign some signatures every slot, and check if each validator in the sync committee is an aggregator every slot).\n\nWe've now included sync committee signature gossip in the batch verification which has reduced CPU usage, but the impact of sync committees will be significantly reduced on MainNet as it will be much less common to be in one at all and very unlikely to be on multiple sync subnets at the same time.\n\nWill investigate if there are any optimisation opportunities when calculating or performing sync committee duties before closing this out.",
