    "created_at": "2021-07-15T01:40:47Z",
    "updated_at": "2021-07-15T01:40:47Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "When running 1000 validators (10% of network) we do see the majority of Cpu usage is signing - nearly 20% of Cpu usage.  There's little that can be done to optimise that but it will be significantly less load on bigger testnets because it will be much less likely that validators will be part of the sync subcommittee.\n\nAt this stage I don't see any signs of performance degradation, and we shouldn't see any significant change to CPU usage on the bigger testnets when Altair activates.",
